WEBVTT

00:03.456 --> 00:04.356
Hey.

00:04.357 --> 00:05.923
Hi, how was the screening?

00:05.925 --> 00:07.725
Oh, Sheldon invoked Rosa Parks

00:07.727 --> 00:10.227
to make somebody who
cut the line feel bad,

00:10.229 --> 00:14.632
but only the
white people felt bad.

00:14.634 --> 00:16.834
Ugh, I should've never bought
him that coloring book

00:16.836 --> 00:19.603
that explains
Black History Month.

00:19.605 --> 00:21.038
How'd it go with my mother?

00:21.040 --> 00:23.073
Uh, you know,
it started a little rocky,

00:23.075 --> 00:24.975
but I think we got
to a good place.

00:24.977 --> 00:26.010
Wow.

00:26.012 --> 00:27.278
Well done.
(chuckles)

00:27.280 --> 00:28.479
Yeah, and when I dropped her off
at the hotel,

00:28.481 --> 00:29.480
she even gave me a hug.

00:29.482 --> 00:32.983
Did she think
you were choking or...

00:32.985 --> 00:34.418
I'm sorry, that's great.

00:34.420 --> 00:36.153
Thank you for
spending time with her.

00:36.155 --> 00:37.621
No problem.

00:37.623 --> 00:39.089
Um, so listen,

00:39.091 --> 00:41.892
I don't know if you have
any plans next weekend,

00:41.894 --> 00:43.694
but I kind of promised your mom

00:43.696 --> 00:45.195
we'd have another
wedding ceremony

00:45.197 --> 00:47.298
so she could attend this time.

00:47.300 --> 00:50.367
Wait, we're gonna
get married again?

00:50.369 --> 00:53.471
Yeah, kind of, but now we can
invite our friends and family.

00:53.472 --> 00:56.173
Seems like a lot
of trouble for a hug.

00:56.174 --> 00:57.373
Come on, it'll be fun,

00:57.375 --> 00:59.008
and, you know, your mom
was genuinely hurt

00:59.010 --> 01:00.676
we didn't invite her
to the first one.

01:00.678 --> 01:02.077
Look, in our defense,

01:02.079 --> 01:04.245
it was kind of a spur
of the moment thing,

01:04.248 --> 01:06.382
and also, we don't like her.

01:06.384 --> 01:07.950
Leonard, come on,
she's your mom.

01:07.952 --> 01:09.985
If we can do something
to make her happy,

01:09.987 --> 01:10.886
why wouldn't we?

01:10.888 --> 01:12.154
I just said why--

01:12.156 --> 01:13.889
we don't like her.

01:13.891 --> 01:15.191
Hey, look,
then forget about her,

01:15.193 --> 01:16.358
let's do it for us.

01:16.360 --> 01:17.693
We could keep it
small and informal.

01:17.695 --> 01:19.161
This time we can
invite our families.

01:19.163 --> 01:20.496
Is your brother out of prison?

01:20.498 --> 01:22.665
Thanks to overcrowding, yeah.

01:22.667 --> 01:25.768
I'd love it
if my dad could come.

01:25.770 --> 01:27.136
Oh, you have to invite him.

01:27.138 --> 01:28.604
I haven't seen him
since the divorce.

01:28.606 --> 01:30.506
Oh, he's like a different man.

01:30.508 --> 01:32.107
Oh.
He stopped twitching,

01:32.109 --> 01:34.577
and I think he grew
an inch and a half.

01:34.579 --> 01:36.478
Well, then it's settled.

01:36.480 --> 01:37.813
Yay.

01:37.815 --> 01:38.814
God.

01:38.816 --> 01:39.982
So funny.

01:39.984 --> 01:42.418
I never thought my second
marriage would be to you!

01:44.121 --> 01:47.756
♪ Our whole universe
was in a hot, dense state ♪

01:47.758 --> 01:51.093
♪ Then nearly 14 billion years
ago expansion started... Wait! ♪

01:51.095 --> 01:52.695
♪ The Earth began to cool ♪

01:52.697 --> 01:55.264
♪ The autotrophs began to drool,
Neanderthals developed tools ♪

01:55.266 --> 01:57.933
♪ We built the Wall ♪
♪ <i>We built the pyramids</i> ♪

01:57.935 --> 02:00.603
♪ Math, Science, History,
unraveling the mystery ♪

02:00.605 --> 02:02.504
♪ That all started
with a big bang ♪

02:02.506 --> 02:04.473
♪ <i>Bang!</i> ♪

02:04.497 --> 02:08.497
<b><font color="#00FF00">♪ The Big Bang Theory 9x24 ♪</font></b>
<font color="#00FFFF">The Convergence Convergence</font>
Original Air D

02:08.520 --> 02:13.521
== sync, corrected by <font color="#00FF00">elderman</font> ==
<font color="#00FFFF">@elder_man</font>

02:13.534 --> 02:15.200
Okay, so it's not
a legal ceremony,

02:15.202 --> 02:16.368
it's just a chance for us

02:16.370 --> 02:18.970
to redo our vows
so everyone can be part of it.

02:18.972 --> 02:22.474
So there's no maid of honor?

02:22.476 --> 02:23.408
No.

02:23.410 --> 02:26.578
Huh.

02:26.580 --> 02:29.881
But if I were to, say,
wear a purple satin dress

02:29.883 --> 02:32.217
with a sweetheart neckline
and stand near you,

02:32.219 --> 02:34.653
you wouldn't be able
to stop me, right?

02:36.190 --> 02:37.656
I don't see how I could.

02:37.658 --> 02:38.657
(chuckles)

02:38.659 --> 02:41.493
Then I graciously accept.

02:41.495 --> 02:42.994
Who's going to officiate?

02:42.996 --> 02:44.696
I was kind of hoping you would.

02:44.698 --> 02:47.599
Wait, now I'm just some
lousy maid of honor?

02:49.002 --> 02:51.269
Hey, good news, I just got off
the phone with my mother.

02:51.271 --> 02:52.337
She is coming to the wedding.

02:52.339 --> 02:54.072
Okay, wait,

02:54.074 --> 02:55.841
you're inviting people
to <i>our</i> wedding?

02:55.843 --> 02:59.745
Yes, I'm inviting
people to <i>our</i> wedding.

02:59.747 --> 03:01.012
Yeah, I've already asked

03:01.014 --> 03:03.382
Stephen Hawking
and Robert Downey Jr.

03:03.384 --> 03:04.983
And now, don't get your hopes
up, 'cause he's pretty busy,

03:04.985 --> 03:07.352
but Erno Rubik.

03:07.354 --> 03:09.354
Who's Erno Rubik?

03:09.356 --> 03:11.857
Seriously?

03:11.859 --> 03:13.325
He invented the Rubik's Cube.

03:13.327 --> 03:15.460
Okay, fine,

03:15.462 --> 03:17.129
but why would you invite him
to our wedding?

03:17.131 --> 03:19.431
Because, despite his fame
and fortune,

03:19.433 --> 03:21.933
he strikes me as a lonely man.

03:21.935 --> 03:24.136
Well, it's very sweet

03:24.138 --> 03:26.338
of you to go to all this trouble
for Leonard's mother.

03:26.340 --> 03:27.939
Yeah, I'm also doing it
for Leonard.

03:27.941 --> 03:29.975
I think this could really help
their relationship.

03:29.977 --> 03:33.145
How dare you invite your father
without consulting me!

03:35.849 --> 03:38.150
Sorry, but I don't think
I need your permission

03:38.152 --> 03:40.285
to have my father at my wedding.

03:40.287 --> 03:42.821
You do understand our marriage
ended because he had an affair.

03:42.823 --> 03:43.889
I know,

03:43.891 --> 03:45.957
and there's no excuse for that.

03:45.959 --> 03:49.528
He claimed I was cold,
emasculating,

03:49.530 --> 03:52.364
and hadn't shown him any
physical affection for years.

03:52.366 --> 03:55.867
I was wrong, there's
three excuses for that.

